At the time of writing this guide, the latest image available for download
 was 'Angstrom-development-GNOME-image-eglibc-ipk-v2012.12-minnow-2013.06.04.img.xz'
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Now, identify the disk device filename for your microSD card.
 You can do this by opening the Disk Utility application (sometimes also
 called Disks) in Ubuntu and clicking on the microSD card entry.
 See the Device field to determine the raw device name of your microSD card.
 Note that this device name should specify an entire disk device (e.g, /dev/sde),
 and not an individual disk partition (e.g, /dev/sde1)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Now, unmount the microSD card by typing the command below in the terminal.
 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\shape italic

\begin_inset Box Boxed
position "t"
hor_pos "c"
has_inner_box 1
inner_pos "t"
use_parbox 0
use_makebox 0
width "100col%"
special "none"
height "1in"
height_special "totalheight"
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\noindent
$ sudo umount /dev/sdX?* 
\end_layout

\end_inset


\shape default

\begin_inset VSpace defskip
\end_inset


\begin_inset VSpace defskip
\end_inset

Here 'sdX' stands for the raw device id of the microSD card.
\end_layout

